# Combine the datasets into a single DataFrame
data_list = []
for name, data in [('live_1', live_1), ('live_2', live_2), ('live_3', live_3),
                   ('fixed_1', fixed_1), ('fixed_2', fixed_2), ('fixed_3', fixed_3)]:
    # Filter data to include 'bin start' > 0 and 'count' < 2000
    filtered_data = data[(data['bin start'] > 0) & (data['count'] < 2000)]
    
    # Apply a Gaussian filter to smooth the 'count' data
    smoothed_count = gaussian_filter1d(filtered_data['count'], sigma=4)
    
    # Calculate the frequency of counts in percentage
    count_frequency = (smoothed_count / smoothed_count.sum()) * 100
    
    # Add to the data list
    data_list.append(pd.DataFrame({
        'bin start': filtered_data['bin start'],
        'frequency': count_frequency*100,
        'dataset': name.split('_')[0],  # Extract 'live' or 'fixed' from the name
        'file': name  # Keep the file name for labeling purposes
    }))

# Combine all datasets into one DataFrame
combined_data = pd.concat(data_list)
